@dev Calculates the reflection rate based on rSupply and rSupply. As
 reflection fees are deducted from rSupply by {_reflectFee} function,
 the reflection rate will decrease, causing users' balances to increase
 by the reflection fee in proportion to the user's balance / total supply

@dev Calculates the scaled up and actual token supply exclusive of
 excluded addresses. This impacts the reflection rate (greater decrease)
 to allow included addresses to receive reflections that would have gone
 to excluded accounts.

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOf(address).details: Overrides ERC20 balanceOf function. If account is excluded then _tOwned balance is returned since that tracks token balance without reflections. Otherwise, _rOwned balance is returned after scaling down by reflection rate.

params.account: is address to be checked for token balance.

params.index: is the acquisition wallet address to be replaced, from 0 to 4.
params.newAddress: is the new address to replace existing acquisition wallet address.
is the new address to replace existing marketing wallet address.

params.acquisition_: is list of initial 5 acquisition wallet addresses.

decimals().details: Overrides ERC20 decimals function. Value of 4 decimals is required to maintain precision of arithmetic operations for reflection fee distributions, given the token supply.

returns._0: decimals_ is number of decimals for display purposes.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

params.account: is address to be excluded from reflections.

params.index: is number between 0 - 4 representing wallets 1 through 5.

params.account: is address to be re-included to reflections.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

params.account: is address to be checked if excluded from reflections.

returns._0: excluded_ is true if account is excluded, otherwise, returns false.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

returns.status: is current pause status. Returns true if contract is paused, otherwise, returns false.

params.exchangePair: is the DEX-created contract address of the exchange pair to be removed as an "exchange" for fee collection.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.acquisitionFee: is the new acquisition fee percentage.
params.marketingFee: is the new marketing fee percentage.
params.reflectFee: is the new reflection fee percentage.

setExchange(address).details: Only transactions to, and from this address will trigger fee collection.

params.exchangePair: is the DEX-created contract address of the exchange pair.

params.acquisitionFee: is the new acquisition fee percentage.
params.marketingFee: is the new marketing fee percentage.
params.reflectFee: is the new reflection fee percentage.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

tokenFromReflection(uint256).details: Helper function for balanceOf function. Scales down a given amount, inclusive of reflections, by reflection rate.

params.rAmount: is the amount, inclusive of reflections, to be scaled down by reflection rate.

returns._0: tAmount_ is amount scaled down by current reflection rate.
totalFees_ is total reflection fees collected.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. Requirements: - `sender` and `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - `sender` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``sender``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: A Fee on Transfer token with automatic reflections to holders.

changeAcquisition(uint256,address).notice: Changes acquisition wallets address to receive acquisition fee going forward. Can only be updated by administrator.

changeMarketing(address).notice: Changes marketing wallet address to receive marketing fee going forward. Can only be updated by administrator.

constructor.notice: Sets the values for name, symbol, totalSupply, marketingWallet, and acquisitionWallets. Initial allocation: 95% to Admin account (for liquidity), 2% to Marketing wallet, 3% to Acquisition wallets.

decimals().notice: Number of decimals for token representation.

excludeAccount(address).notice: Removes address from receiving future reflection distributions. Can only be updated by administrator.

getAcquisitionWallet(uint256).notice: Returns which address is receiving acquisition fees from 'BUY' / 'SELL' transactions at a given index.

getMarketingWallet().notice: Returns which address is receiving marketing fees from 'BUY' / 'SELL' transactions.

includeAccount(address).notice: Includes previously excluded address to receive reflection distributions in case of erroneously excluded address. NOTE: Included address will receive all previous reflection distribution it should have received while address was excluded. Can only be updated by administrator.

isExcluded(address).notice: Allows checking whether an account has been excluded from receiving reflection distributions.

lockToken().notice: Pauses token transfer functionality in case of emergency. Can only be updated by administrator.

removeExchange(address).notice: Removes an exchange pair address from fee collection. Can only be updated by administrator.

setBuyFees(uint8,uint8,uint8).notice: Changes the reflection, marketing, and acquisition fee percentages to be deducted from 'BUY' transaction type. Can only be updated by administrator.

setExchange(address).notice: Sets the exchange pair address for the token to detect 'BUY', 'SELL', or 'NONE' transactions for fee collection. Can only be updated by administrator.

setSellFees(uint8,uint8,uint8).notice: Changes the reflection, marketing, and acquisition fee percentages to be deducted from {SELL} transaction type. Can only be updated by administrator.

tokenFromReflection(uint256).notice: Provides scaled down amount based on current reflection rate.

totalFees().notice: Allows to view total amount of reflection fees collected since contract creation.

unlockToken().notice: Unpauses token transfer functionality to allow users to transfer token. Can only be updated by administrator.

userdoc.notice: Token contract inheriting ERC20 standard with basic access control and emergency pause mechanism. The token contract implements Fee on Transfer distributed among marketing wallet, acquisition wallets, and all token holders (via reflections) on Buy / Sell transactions only. Wallet-to-wallet transfers do not incur a fee on transfer.
